cess is broken and is going to need researchers, scientists, urban planners, environmentalists and concerned citizens everywhere to fix it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"We need to engage our scientific, technology, and environmental communities to deconstruct and re-imagine the entire process with a fresh mind and an entirely new set of eyes and stop focusing so much of our attention at the tail end of the consumer process and start looking hard at the front end."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"As the earth’s resources remain threatened or as prices increase to dispose of these recyclables in a non-sustainable method, we can either choose to continue down the expected path or reimagine a better outcome."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The article in its entirety was posted on 11/16/2015 and can be found here:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/rick-fedrizzi/rethinking-recycling-a-ca_b_8574932.html?utm_source=Sailthru&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=Issue:%202015-11-17%20Waste%20Dive%20Newsletter&utm_term=Waste%20Dive","target":null}}],"text":"http://www.huffingtonpost.com/rick-fedrizzi/rethinking-recycling-a-ca_b_8574932.html?utm_source=Sailthru&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=Issue:%202015-11-17%20Waste%20Dive%20Newsletter&utm_term=Waste%20Dive"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" "}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":" "}]}]}}